An aggrieved fan has called out singer Wande Coal for not allegedly keeping his N1m promise over a music video he made. He claimed the singer made a N1m promise to anyone who has the highest views on social media with his song titled ‘gentility’. The fan added screenshots of the promises by Wande Coal, asking him to redeem his image.   Portable storms buka after headies nominations     Fighting Bobrisky amounts to rolling in mud – Tonto…     30 Nigerian celebrities made by reality shows   He wrote: “Wande Coal, the story no clear. You actually promised a million naira for the best video for your Gentility song. Bro I got over 3.5 million views on this same song, that’s one of my videos because I did several which is the highest views on TikTok for that Gentility song. Bro your song hit Top 1 for Apple music, Baba you don cash out. “Baba we no hear anything for the money, I say make I ask how far wetin dey sup about the money, the story no clear bros. Clear us, where the money dey because na me get highest views o and I get highest likes. Where the money dey bros?”